==English==

===Noun===
'''hypallage'''
# A a [[literary device]] that is the reversal of the syntactic relation of two words (as in "her beauty's face")
eg. ''I can't knock the smirk of his stupid face'' is a hypallage, because the thing that is referred to being stupid is "him", and not "his face"

